ca_np<-read_csv(here("data","ca_np.csv"))
## Rows: 789 Columns: 7
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (5): region, state, code, park_name, type
## dbl (2): visitors, year
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
ci_np<-read_excel(here("data","ci_np.xlsx"))
ggbase<-ggplot(data=ci_np,aes(x = year, y=visitors))
ggbase +
  geom_line(
  color = "purple",
  linetype = "dashed"
  )

ggbase+
  geom_point(
    color="red",
    shape=19,
    alpha=0.3,
  )

ggbase+geom_col()

ggbase+geom_area()

ggbase +
  geom_point(
    aes(size = visitors,
        color = visitors),
    alpha = 0.5
  )+ theme_light()

ggbase +
  geom_point(
    aes(size = visitors,
        color = visitors),
    alpha = 0.5
  )+ theme_bw()

ggbase + geom_line(linetype="dotted")+theme_bw()+labs(title="Channel Islands Annual Visitors",subtitle = "1963-2016")

ggnp<-ggplot(data=ca_np, aes(x=year, y =visitors, group = park_name))
ggnp+geom_line(show.legend=FALSE) + theme_light()+facet_wrap(~park_name) +labs(x = "year", y = "annual visitors")
